'''Latvijas Balzams''' ({{lang-en|[[Latvia]]n [[Balsam (drink)|Balsam]]}}) is the largest [[alcoholic beverage]] producer in the [[Baltic states]] headquartered in [[Riga]].<ref name="QuarterlyReport2014-1" />{{rp|2}} {{As of|2006}}, it had a market share of about 50% in Latvia.<ref name="Culture and Customs of the Baltic States 0313331251" />{{rp|110}} The company has a long history as the beginning of it can be considered 1900 when Riga State Spirits Warehouse No.1 started operation as it later changed its name to Latvijas balzams in 1970 and eventually became a public joint stock company in 1997.<ref name="History" /> Its flagship product is [[Riga Black Balsam]] which is a traditional Latvian [[herbal liqueur]].
