'''Ndonga''', also called '''Oshindonga''', is a [[Bantu languages|Bantu]] language spoken in [[Namibia]] and parts of [[Angola]]. It is a standardized [[dialect]] of the [[Ovambo language]], and is [[mutual intelligibility|mutually intelligible]] with [[Kwanyama dialect|Kwanyama]], the other Ovambo dialect with a standard written form. With 281,500 speakers, the language has the largest number of speakers in Namibia.  

[[Martti Rautanen]] translated the [[Bible]] into the Ndonga standard.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.namibweb.com/olukonda.htm |title=Namiweb.com |publisher=Namibweb.com |date= |accessdate=2013-03-16}}</ref>

