'''Petrolimex Joint Stock Insurance Company''' (PJICO) is state-owned insurance company in [[Vietnam]], involved in the non-life insurance market. The company's stock is currently not listed on the [[Ho Chi Minh City Securities Trading Center]] and it is majority-owned by [[Petrolimex]] (51%), a state-owned petroleum company. The company is headquartered in [[Ha Noi]] and has 49 branches most of Vietnam's provinces. PJICO is the fourth largest insurance provider in Vietnam, and it is the third largest non-life insurer.<ref>{{cite news |title=Insurance In Focus |url=http://www.alacrastore.com/storecontent/Business-and-Industry/133184806 |work=Vietnam Investment Review |date=23 May 2005 |accessdate=2009-01-21 }}</ref> It had a share of around 10% in the insurance market (excluding life insurance) in 2011, making it fourth after [[Bao Viet Insurance]], [[PetroVietnam Insurance]] and [[Bao Minh]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Cơ hội nào cho nhà đầu tư chiến lược mới tại Bảo Việt?|url=http://gafin.vn/20121219112947641p0c36/co-hoi-nao-cho-nha-dau-tu-chien-luoc-moi-tai-bao-viet.htm|accessdate=20 December 2012|newspaper=GaFin.vn|date=20 December 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121221013853/http://gafin.vn/20121219112947641p0c36/co-hoi-nao-cho-nha-dau-tu-chien-luoc-moi-tai-bao-viet.htm|archivedate=21 December 2012|df=}}</ref> 

