{{Infobox company | name = Perum Peruri | type = Perusahaan Umum | foundation = 15 September 1971 | founder = Indonesia Government | location = [[Jakarta]], Indonesia | key_people = [[Dwina Septiani Wijaya]], CEO, [[Rizal Affandi Lukman]], President Commissioner | industry = Indonesia Integrated Security Printing and System | revenue = {{profit}} [[Indonesian Rupiah|Rp]] Rp 2.410 Trilyun (2016) | operating_income = {{profit}} Rp 287 Milyar (2016) | equity = {{profit}} Rp 2.033 Trilyun (2016) | assets = {{profit}} Rp 3.639 Trilyun (2016) | net_income = {{profit}} [[Indonesian Rupiah|Rp]] Rp 161 Milyar (2016) | num_employees = 1,688 <small>(2016)</small> | homepage = [http://www.peruri.co.id/ www.peruri.co.id] }}
'''Perum Peruri''' (short for ''Perum Percetakan Uang Republik Indonesia'', ''Money Printing Public Company of the [[Indonesia|Republic of Indonesia]]'') is the Indonesian state banknote/[[Security printing|security printer]]s and [[Mint (coin)|mint]], established on 15 September 1971 through the merger of state mint ''Artha Yasa'' and state printers ''Pertjetakan Kebajoran'' (a.k.a. Perkeba).
Printers Pertjetakan Kebajoran had originally been established with assistance from [[Netherlands|Dutch]] banknote printers [[Joh. Enschedé]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Royal Joh. Enschedé - Museum|url=http://www.joh-enschede.com/?page=joh.news.museum|accessdate=20 March 2013}}</ref>
It has offices in [[Jakarta]], [[Karawang]] and [[Surabaya]], with marketing and administrative functions taking place in Jakarta, and printing and minting occurring in Karawang and Surabaya.
Since 2007, Perum Peruri has also been printing [[Nepalese Rupees]] and in 2005, the company began making Malaysian [[ringgit]] coins and [[passports]].<ref>http://majalah.tempointeraktif.com/id/arsip/2010/05/03/EB/mbm.20100503.EB133448.id.html</ref>
