{{Infobox diocese |jurisdiction = Diocese |name = Kamina |latin = Dioecesis Kaminaensis |country = {{flag|Democratic Republic of the Congo}} |metropolitan = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Lubumbashi|Lubumbashi]] |rite = [[Latin Rite]] |cathedral = |cocathedral = |area_km2 = 73,479 |population = 746,223 |population_as_of = 2003 |catholics = 199,916 |catholics_percent= 26.8 |pope = {{Incumbent pope}} |bishop = [[Jean-Anatole Kalala Kaseba]] |coadjutor = |auxiliary_bishops= }}
The '''Roman Catholic Diocese of Kamina''' ({{lang-la|Kainaën(sis)}}) is a [[diocese]] located in the city of [[Kamina]] in the [[Ecclesiastical province]] of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Lubumbashi|Lubumbashi]] in the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]].
==History== * July 18, 1922: Established as Apostolic Prefecture of Lulua and Central Katanga from the [[Apostolic Vicariate of Upper Kasai]] and [[Apostolic Prefecture of Katanga]] * February 26, 1934: Promoted as Apostolic Vicariate of Lulua and Central Katanga * July 8, 1948: Renamed as Apostolic Vicariate of Lulua * November 10, 1959: Promoted as Diocese of Kamina
==Leadership== * [[Bishop]]s of Kamina (Latin Rite) ** Bishop Jean-Anatole Kalala Kaseba (since 1990.01.22) ** Bishop [[Barthélémy Malunga]] (1971.03.11 – 1990.01.22) ** Bishop [[Victor Petrus Keuppens]], [[Order of Friars Minor|O.F.M.]] (1959.11.10 – 1971.03.11) * Vicars Apostolic of Lulua (Latin Rite) ** Bishop Victor Petrus Keuppens, O.F.M. (1950.06.25 – 1959.11.10) ** Bishop [[Camillo Paolo A. Stappers]], O.F.M. (1934.02.26 – 1949) * Prefects Apostolic of Lulua and Central Katanga (Latin Rite) ** Bishop Camillo Paolo A. Stappers, O.F.M. (1922 – 1934.02.26)
