The '''Roman Catholic Diocese of Pankshin''' ({{lang-la|Pankshinen(sis)}}) is a [[diocese]] located in the city of [[Pankshin]] in the [[Ecclesiastical province]] of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Jos|Jos]] in [[Nigeria]].
==History== On 18 March 18 2014 the Diocese of Pankshin was established from territory of the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Jos|Archdiocese of Jos]] and the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Shendam|Diocese of Shendam]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.news.va/en/news/africanigeria-erection-of-the-diocese-of-pankshin | title=Erection of the Diocese of Pankshin and appointment of the first Bishop | publisher=The Holy See News Portal (News.va) | accessdate=28 July 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/dpank.html | title=Diocese of Pankshin | publisher=[[Catholic Hierarchy]] | accessdate=28 July 2014}}</ref>
